CS PSI-STALKER

CS Psi-Stalkers are Coalition States psionic mutant humans bred and trained
to track, locate, and destroy supernatural beings, psionics, and magic users.
Like Dog Boys, they are a Coalition creation: but unlike Dog Boys, Psi-
Stalkers are valued as specialists rather than as expendable soldiers.  They
feed on psionic energy drained from their prey, which grants them a sixth
sense for detecting anything supernatural.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 7-22   MA: 3-18   PS: 7-22 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 7-22   PB: 4-14   Spd: 7-22

DAMAGE POOL:
  SDC: 2d6 x10 (approx 20-120)

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - Psionic bloodhound: sense and track any psionic or magical being
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Feed on psionic energy: drain ISP/PPE from living beings to sustain self
  - Enhanced ME, PS, PE, PP, and Spd

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible, Coalition training defines the path
  - Must feed on psionic energy regularly; without it suffers penalties
  - Psychological conditioning for Coalition loyalty

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any (Coalition Psi-Stalkers tend toward Anarchist or Scrupulous).

See also: dog_boy, mind_melter, burster, races
